Yes—drop the Spring-style application annotations. In this codebase they create more than marginal complexity: C++ reflection, a regex scanner/code generator, CMake integration, generated registration functions, and annotation-specific runtime paths all exist to avoid explicit registration.

The main complication is that “annotations” currently cover separate concerns:

| Area | Recommendation |
|---|---|
| DI, controllers, routes, lifecycle, exception advice | Replace with fluent builders |
| REST-client interfaces/codegen | Replace with an explicit client builder |
| Validation | Replace with an explicit validator schema/builder |
| ODB persistence metadata | Migrate separately; use native ODB pragmas first, rather than forcing a builder |
| Lombok generation | Treat as independent; retain temporarily or replace with ordinary C++ |

The highest-value removal targets are [attributes.h](/home/uday/Projects/novaboot/include/novaboot/di/attributes.h), [web_attributes.h](/home/uday/Projects/novaboot/include/novaboot/router/web_attributes.h), the reflection-heavy registration code in [container.h](/home/uday/Projects/novaboot/include/novaboot/di/container.h), and the regex scanner in [di_scanner.cpp](/home/uday/Projects/novaboot/src/tools/di_scanner.cpp). The scanner currently also writes source files into app directories for REST clients, which is especially brittle.

## Plan

1. Define the replacement API and acceptance criteria.
   - DI: `singleton<T>(factory)`, `request<T>(factory)`, `bind<Interface>().to<Implementation>()`, lifecycle callbacks, qualifiers, lazy/async options.
   - Web: explicit route groups and method handlers, with a reusable typed `di::handler<&Controller::method>()` adapter.
   - Exceptions: `.on_exception<Exception>(handler)`.
   - Client: `RestClient::builder().base_url(...).protocol(...).build()`; application-owned client wrappers call it directly.
   - Validation: `Validator<User>{}.field(&User::name, "name").not_empty().size(2, 20)`.

2. Build the fluent DI API without reflection.
   - Preserve the existing explicit `register_bean` core as the implementation base.
   - Add ergonomic builder wrappers, interface bindings, scopes, lifecycle hooks, and startup validation.
   - Remove reflection constructor discovery and require explicit factories. This makes dependencies and ownership visible at the composition root.

3. Build typed fluent routing and exception registration.
   - Extend the existing [Router::RouteBuilder](/home/uday/Projects/novaboot/include/novaboot/router/router.h) rather than introduce a second router API.
   - Extract/reuse the current controller argument binding and response serialization machinery from [Server](/home/uday/Projects/novaboot/include/novaboot/core/server.h).
   - Migrate the server example from annotated `UserController` routes to explicit grouped routes.

4. Migrate both examples completely.
   - Replace `novaboot_di_register_all()` and `novaboot_web_register_all()` in [server main](/home/uday/Projects/novaboot/examples/server/src/main.cpp) and the client example.
   - Convert lifecycle annotations to `.on_start()` / `.on_stop()`.
   - Convert `ControllerAdvice` to explicit exception handlers.
   - Convert REST-client generated interfaces into normal client classes.

5. Remove application-wiring codegen.
   - Delete `novaboot_auto_scan`, `novaboot_di_scan`, scanner-driven DI/web generation, and REST-client sidecar generation.
   - Remove `-freflection` as a framework-wide requirement once no remaining framework feature needs it.
   - Update CMake and examples so builds have no hidden source discovery.

6. Decouple validation and persistence.
   - Introduce validator schemas and migrate current validation tests/models.
   - For ODB, first replace NovaBoot data attributes with direct ODB pragmas and delete the annotation translation bridge. Don’t mix this with the DI/routing migration—it is a distinct persistence decision.
   - Decide separately whether Lombok remains as an optional codegen tool; it is not part of the Spring-style wiring problem.

7. Verify and delete legacy support.
   - Add focused tests for DI registration, scopes, lifecycle ordering, typed handler argument binding, exception mapping, client configuration, and validator schemas.
   - Port integration tests/examples.
   - Delete old annotation headers, reflection helpers, scanner target, scanner CMake module, ODB bridge, and annotation-only tests only after parity is proven.

I’d make this a clean breaking change rather than maintaining annotations and fluent APIs indefinitely. A short compatibility branch is reasonable for migrating examples, but dual first-class APIs would preserve most of the complexity you’re trying to remove.